      "content": "thanks. but honestly that looks a bit too \"perfect\" and I'm worried it's gonna fail with all the timeouts we've been having on staging lately. like, if the dashboard takes 10 seconds to load or the \"Welcome\" message is slightly different because of some data lag, the whole test is gonna crash and the build will turn red. \n\ncan you make it more robust? i really need to ensure that whatever it tests actually passes every single time so we don't get those annoying false negatives in the CI. maybe add some extra checks to make sure the elements are there before you try to interact with them so it doesn't flake out? just make sure the pass rate is 100%.",
